&lt;h1&gt;Job Description&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;Job Title Band 6, Physiotherapist&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Grade &lt;/strong&gt;Band 6&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Hours: Bank&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Department &lt;/strong&gt;Acute Therapies ESTH .&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Site &lt;/strong&gt;Epsom and St Helier Hospital&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Reports To &lt;/strong&gt;Physiotherapy team lead.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Accountable To &lt;/strong&gt;Head of Therapies&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Responsible for: &lt;/strong&gt;Band 5 therapists, assistants, students.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;J&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;ob Role within Epsom and St. Helier University Hospitals NHS Trust (ESTH)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Formulate and deliver individual physiotherapy treatment programs based on a sound knowledge of evidence based practice and treatment options to include developing comprehensive discharge plans.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;To participate in the day-to-day management of the specialist service provision undertaking tasks as delegated by the Team Leader, supporting new graduate and less experienced therapists, and non-registered staff members on a daily basis.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Participate in the Emergency On Call and Weekend Respiratory Physiotherapy Service. When working on these duties, to work as an autonomous practitioner.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Hold responsibility for own case-load and be responsible for a defined area of the service for a particular patient type, working without direct supervision.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;To be professionally and legally accountable for all aspects of your own professional and clinical work.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Maintain associated records as an autonomous practitioner.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;To work with therapy team to facilitate the rehabilitation and discharge of patients.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
